---
title: Sausage Flatbread Dinner with a Tomato Pasta for Lunch
description: Cook it once, eat it twice: tonight’s dinner extras transform into tomorrow’s lunch. That’s thanks to special added ingredients that can easily be heated up, even at the office (your coworkers will be amazed, trust us). The first dish in this 2-in-1 recipe is a hearty sausage and zucchini pizza that packs plenty of flavor into each slice. The next day, the rest of the toppings are used to make a sophisticated pasta with plenty of Parmesan on top. *The nutrient information for the Tomato Pasta Lunch is as follows: Calories 770, Fat 38 g, Saturated Fat 18 g, Cholesterol 220 mg, Sodium 1840 mg, Carbs 81 g, Fiber 6 g, Sugar 10 g, and Protein 39 g. The nutrition facts panel below represents the nutrient values for the Sausage Pizza Dinner*
